(Focused on analytics + ledger-based latency)

Routing Analytics Module

Ledger-grounded latency measurement for public accountability.

This module does not infer workflow state.

It measures factual time between immutable events.

If this module guesses instead of measures, your transparency becomes fiction.

Core Principle

Metrics must be ledger-derived.
Latency must be event-based.
No inferred workflow shortcuts.

Public analytics must be defensible under replay.

Domain Responsibility

This module owns:

Ledger-based latency computation

Event-bound time measurement

Public-facing response speed analytics

It does not:

Infer lifecycle transitions

Query case tables

Inspect execution state columns

Derive workflow state

Mutate ledger

Mutate cases

It reads immutable history and computes duration.

Latency Definition

Latency is defined as:

EXECUTION_COMPLETED.ts - CASE_CREATED.ts

These are:

Factual ledger events

Immutable

Replay-safe

Timestamped at commit

This prevents:

Drift from projection tables

Manual lifecycle overrides

Analytics corruption

Why Ledger Instead of Tables?

Because:

Tables reflect projection state.
Ledger reflects historical fact.

Tables can be repaired.
Ledger cannot be rewritten.

If analytics depend on projection:

You measure what the system thinks happened.

If analytics depend on ledger:

You measure what actually happened.

For public trust, that distinction matters.

Implementation Characteristics

calculateLatency(postWinId)

Flow:

Fetch audit trail from LedgerService

Find CASE_CREATED event

Find EXECUTION_COMPLETED event

Normalize timestamp (number | bigint)

Compute delta in milliseconds

No inference.
No fallback logic.
No lifecycle assumptions.

If either event missing → return 0.

Zero means: insufficient factual boundary.

Invariants

LedgerService must return ordered audit trail.

Timestamps must represent canonical commit time.

Event types must be immutable enum values.

Latency calculation must remain pure.

No database writes.

No derived state mutation.

Break these and analytics become misleading.

Edge Case Handling

Missing CASE_CREATED
→ return 0

Missing EXECUTION_COMPLETED
→ return 0

Bigint timestamp
→ normalized safely

This prevents:

Runtime crashes

Partial data leakage

Inconsistent analytics output

Public metrics must degrade safely.

Time Units

Returned value: milliseconds.

Conversion responsibility belongs to:

API mapper

Frontend

Reporting layer

Do not embed presentation formatting here.

Analytics layer computes fact.
Presentation layer formats narrative.

Failure Modes Considered

Ledger trail empty
→ return 0

Unexpected timestamp type
→ safe normalization

Event ordering unexpected
→ find() ensures first match

Multiple execution completions
→ first match used (authoritative earliest boundary)

If multiple completions possible,
clarify which event represents final authority.

Scalability Considerations

Current complexity:

O(n) over audit trail

If ledger grows large:

Options:

Add indexed query for specific event types

Add ledgerService.getFirstEventOfType()

Pre-aggregate analytics view

Maintain analytics snapshot table

But never compromise:

Ledger must remain the source of truth.

Why No Workflow Inference?

Because analytics must not depend on:

Lifecycle enums

Projection tables

Milestone counts

Verification state

Decision outcomes

Analytics must measure what happened,
not what the system believes happened.

Inference corrupts public transparency.

Observability Philosophy

Public response speed is a governance signal.

It should answer:

“How long did this case take from intake to execution completion?”

Not:

“How long did our UI think it was active?”

Ledger timestamps are constitutional.

Security Considerations

This module must not:

Expose raw audit trail

Leak actor identities

Leak authority proofs

Leak payload content

Latency is a derived metric.

Return duration, not internal state.

Mental Model

If someone challenges your public performance report,
you must be able to:

Replay the ledger.
Extract CASE_CREATED.
Extract EXECUTION_COMPLETED.
Subtract timestamps.
Produce identical result.

If you cannot do that,
your analytics are storytelling.

This module ensures they are mathematics.
